Hi from Izzy in Anchorage
Hi <@1273045693342285846>. I used to live in Anchorage. Jan 2020- Dec 2021. Even though it was mostly during Covid...loved it up there. Got a lot of hiking in.
Hi Izzy, I am so happy to see another Alaskan here üéâ üíô
Hi Russell, nice to meet you üéâüíô
üòÄüòÄüíôüòÄüòÄ

Hi Zunny. Nice to meet you as well. How are things looking up there? Is Kelly Tschibaka running for anything up there this time around? I know she's (R) so you may not know. Just curious. I used to work for her and I know she ran against Lisa Murkowski last time around and lost.
Can I ask why you are volunteering for the Democrat campaign?

That is a loaded question you just asked. She is part of the problem. I think she is in the Valley. She is doing a podcast or show of sort with her husband. I am sure you can find it online. Project 2025 started here in Alaska long ago, as you must already be aware of, I am somewhat surprised to see you one this side of the aisle. I am quite perplexed actually.

LOL I only said I worked for her. We were friends but I had to distance myself from her in 2020 when she started agreeing with the "stolen election" theory in 2020. And then when she was running for Senate and appeared with Trump...that was pretty much THE END. Even though I don't live there...I'm glad Murkowski won...even though she's (R) she seems very much in the middle and we're losing too many of middle (R)'s. I mean I'd rather it be (D) but if it can't be (D) it needs to at least be middle (R).

I would call myself an independent. When I am voting, I tend to lean (D) but if there is an issue I'm particular about, I will look at all candidates for a specific race and go with the candidate that is closest to me. In other words, I'm true to country before party. That said, I have yet to vote for an (R) in a presidential or congressional race, but I have considered (R)'s in some local races where I have lived because in those instances the (D)'s running had some unusual positions. Hope that makes sense.

That's interesting about Project 2025 starting there. I would have guessed it started in the south. 

Normally I would not get involved other than to donate money towards the cause....but Trump just CANNOT win this year....and it can't be close. It needs to be by a WIDE margin, especially in the swing states. People cannot sit home and not vote this time around and "hope for the best".
